1
00:00:21,320 --> 00:00:22,960
-(NEIGHING)
-Whoa!

2
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:31,080
-Stand and deliver.
-Do as he says.

3
00:00:31,360 --> 00:00:32,480
I've heard of this brigand.

4
00:00:32,840 --> 00:00:34,080
He is known as the Knightmare.

5
00:00:34,160 --> 00:00:35,560
Faster than Sam Swift the Quick.

6
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:36,920
Deadlier than Deadly Dupont...

7
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:40,240
Dabbling lowpads, the pair of them!
With terrible pseudonyms to boot.

8
00:00:40,520 --> 00:00:41,800
Cash bags, jewels, the lot.

9
00:00:41,880 --> 00:00:46,080
I will not be robbed
by some lone ranting cavalier.

10
00:00:46,800 --> 00:00:48,280
Who says I am alone?

11
00:00:51,360 --> 00:00:52,800
(SCREAMING)

12
00:01:05,320 --> 00:01:07,400
-Right.
-(SCANNER BEEPING)

13
00:01:10,160 --> 00:01:11,160
Warm...

14
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:14,880
Warmer.

15
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:19,520
We are cursed. The Knightmare
is in league with the devil.

16
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:22,040
Aye, Satan's sidekick, me.

17
00:01:23,040 --> 00:01:24,320
Where's the rest?

18
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:25,920
What else would you take from me, sir?

19
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:28,720
You know what I want.
Hand over the amulet.

20
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:29,840
-DOCTOR: Hello.
-(MAN YELLS)

21
00:01:29,920 --> 00:01:32,440
Oh, sorry. Chill it.
Don't mind me, don't mind me.

22
00:01:32,520 --> 00:01:34,880
I'm only going to be a minute.
Don't worry. Oh, very warm.

23
00:01:34,960 --> 00:01:36,760
-HIGHWAYMAN: What are you doing?
-Oh, just ignore me,

24
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:38,520
I'm just passing through,
like fish in the night...

25
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:39,640
This is a robbery!

26
00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:40,800
Not fish in the night.

27
00:01:40,880 --> 00:01:42,320
-No, it's something else.
-This is my robbery.

28
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:44,640
No, ships in the night, yeah,
something like that.

29
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:47,000
Step aside
or I shall blow your brains out.

30
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:49,760
Sorry, were you talking to me there?

31
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:51,480
Try again, I promise
I'll listen this time.

32
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:54,600
You have interrupted my robbery, sir,
and you will step away,

33
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:55,800
if you wish to take another breath.

34
00:01:55,880 --> 00:01:57,920
You're going to get us all killed
if you don't shut your mouth.

35
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,800
Sorry, sorry, I really was planning
to listen that time.

36
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:02,640
-But, basically, uh, I didn't.
-(SCANNER BEEPING)

37
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:05,200
Usually someone hits me at this point,

38
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:07,280
but she's taking
the year sevens for tae Kwon do.

39
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:09,480
Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh!

40
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,360
Yes! Got You!

41
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:12,440
Ha-ha!

42
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:15,560
Oh, hang on. If I didn't know better,
I'd say this was a robbery.

43
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:19,120
I am robbing these people,
you are getting out of my way.

44
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:20,760
I just need one tiny little thing
from out of this box.

45
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:23,120
-This is my robbery.
-Well, can't we share it?

46
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:25,000
-Isn't that what robbery's all about?
-COACHMAN: Hyaa!

47
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:26,880
-Hyaa!
-Oh, no, no!

48
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:28,160
No, no, no, no, no!

49
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:29,480
You bungled my heist.

50
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:31,800
No, you bungled mine, Zorro!

51
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:32,880
Whey-faced fool!

52
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:34,400
Yeah, well, why don't you
show your face?

53
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:36,600
At least I show my face,
what's wrong with yours?

54
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:38,600
(GIRL'S VOICE) Nothing, Doctor.

55
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:52,960
-You?
-Yes.

56
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:54,880
It is me.

57
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:57,560
What took you so long, old man?

58
00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:59,720
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

59
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:40,880
-"Old man?”
-Seemed apt.

60
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:44,240
Life expectancy is 35 these days.

61
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:46,000
Well, for everyone else.

62
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:47,480
-But didn't you know it was me?
-Of course.

63
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:49,720
You don't forget the man
who saved your life.

64
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:52,320
-It's good to see you.
-Yes, I didn't get that impression

65
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:53,920
when you were threatening to kill me.

66
00:03:54,160 --> 00:03:56,160
(MAN'S VOICE) The Knightmare
has a reputation to maintain.

67
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,680
That's a very good voice.
How do you do that?

68
00:03:57,760 --> 00:03:58,760
Practise.

69
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:02,040
Last time I saw you,
you were founding a leper colony.

70
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:03,840
I was so proud of you.

71
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,920
Proud of me? You weren't even there.

72
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,520
Yes, I was.

73
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:09,760
You didn't see me, but I saw you.

74
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,240
And you just left me there?

75
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:12,560
Well, you seemed fine.

76
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:13,880
In a leper colony?

77
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:16,960
No matter.

78
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:19,000
You're here now. We should celebrate.

79
00:04:19,080 --> 00:04:22,160
Oh, no, this isn't a visit.
I've got a job to do.

80
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:24,560
I'm here looking for an alien object,

81
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:27,600
which has no business
being here on earth in 1651.

82
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:30,400
It was just... It just so happened,
you know, that my tracking device,

83
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:32,840
it led me to the carriage that you were,

84
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:34,880
you know, robbing.
There wasn't, I didn't, it was...

85
00:04:34,960 --> 00:04:36,320
You mean...

86
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:38,080
You haven't come for me?

87
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:40,240
No, it was just a coincidence.

88
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:45,640
Oh, Ashildr, I'm sorry.

89
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:48,120
Who's Ashildr?

90
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,680
You are. That's your name.

91
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:52,120
Ashildr.

92
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,680
Daughter of Einarr.

93
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:56,200
Chuckles. I used to call him Chuckles.
Do you remember that?

94
00:04:56,640 --> 00:04:57,760
Yes.

95
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:00,200
I think I remember the village.

96
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:01,600
You loved that village.

97
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:03,480
If you say so.

98
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:05,880
Anyone in that village
would have died for you.

99
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:10,120
Well, they're all dead now
and here I am.

100
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:11,480
So, I guess it all worked out.

101
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:13,560
-Ashildr...
-That's not my name.

102
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:16,760
I don't even remember that name.

103
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:21,040
(STAMMERING) Well,
what do you call yourself?

104
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:23,840
-Me.
-Yes, you. There's nobody else here.

105
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:25,040
No.

106
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:26,600
I call myself "Me".

107
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:29,520
All the other names I chose died
with whoever knew me.

108
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:30,720
Me is who I am now.

109
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:33,360
No one's mother, daughter, wife.

110
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:35,400
My own companion.

111
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:38,800
Singular. Unattached.

112
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:40,840
Alone.

113
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:44,240
Anyway, I should get started.

114
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:47,400
Jump on, I'll give you a ride.
You can help me.

115
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:48,800
With what?

116
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:50,400
Packing.

117
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:57,080
Come on.

118
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:02,400
It's a big place for someone
who lives on their own.

119
00:06:03,760 --> 00:06:04,880
I have a servant.

120
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:07,720
And all matters of visitors drop in.

121
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:09,880
(CREATURE SNARLING)

122
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:14,320
(SNARLING CONTINUES)

123
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:23,160
Your device,

124
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:25,480
what is it?

125
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:26,840
My curioscanner.

126
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:30,760
Oh, it sort of, it scans for,
it scans for curios.

127
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:32,240
I just realised how it got its name.

128
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:35,360
It's been tracking exoplanetary energy
for the last couple of weeks.

129
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:38,160
I've been following it
across the galaxy.

130
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,600
And do you know what you're looking for?

131
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:43,320
I've got a pretty good idea. Yes. Why?

132
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:46,080
I wasn't just robbing Lucie Fanshawe
for her loot.

133
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:48,960
She's bragged about having
the rarest gem in the land.

134
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:51,320
An ancient amulet from foreign parts.

135
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:53,920
Could it be we are
looking for the same prize?

136
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:55,680
Clearly, you don't need money.

137
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:57,080
So, why do you rob?

138
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:58,720
For the adventure, Doctor.

139
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:01,800
Isn't that what life's all about?

140
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:04,920
I've had 800 years of adventure.

141
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:07,760
Enough to fill a library
if you write it down.

142
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:11,840
A medieval queen? How exciting.

143
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:13,440
You'd think.

144
00:07:13,840 --> 00:07:16,480
It was paperwork and backgammon mainly,
as I recall.

145
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:18,600
Ended up faking my own death.

146
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:21,440
Did a bunk before the evisceration.

147
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:25,640
Now this was much more my thing.

148
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:29,240
The battle of Agincourt.
My first stint as a man.

149
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:33,240
No one will ever know that a mere woman
helped end the Hundred Years' War.

150
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:34,880
DOCTOR: You're immortal
not indestructible.

151
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:36,160
You can be hurt.

152
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:37,480
Killed even.

153
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:40,880
Ten thousand hours is all it takes
to master any skill.

154
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:43,720
Over 100,000 hours
and you're the best there's ever been.

155
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:45,480
I don't need to be indestructible.

156
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:46,920
I'm superb.

157
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,840
You should have seen me.

158
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:52,080
I could shoot six arrows a minute,
got so close to the enemy,

159
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:53,400
I penetrated arm our.

160
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:55,480
How many people have you killed?

161
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:57,200
You'll have to check my diaries.

162
00:07:57,280 --> 00:07:58,440
You can't remember.

163
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:02,480
For what it's worth,
I've saved many lives, too.

164
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:06,080
I cured an entire village
of scarlet fever once.

165
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:08,880
Almost got drowned
as a witch for my troubles.

166
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:13,240
Fortunately,
I'm really good at holding my breath.

167
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:15,680
Ungrateful peasants.

168
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:16,760
The Black Death.

169
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:18,880
1348.

170
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:22,160
-I meant to warn you.
-I got sick.

171
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,320
But I got better.

172
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:24,600
Of course.

173
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:26,800
Your immune system is learning, too.

174
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:29,000
There's another bout coming.

175
00:08:29,720 --> 00:08:31,760
And a big fire
that tears through London.

176
00:08:31,840 --> 00:08:32,920
Excellent.

177
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,720
-Maybe I start it.
-No, that was the Terileptils.

178
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:38,960
Surgeon, scientist,
inventor, composer...

179
00:08:39,040 --> 00:08:40,280
It's a fantastic CV.

180
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:41,480
You should try my journals.

181
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:43,280
I read them myself now and then.

182
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:47,480
Drink pomace wine.
Have a little me time.

183
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:49,240
You don't seem the nostalgic type.

184
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:50,400
It's not nostalgia,

185
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:52,760
it's curiosity.

186
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:55,360
I can't remember most of it.

187
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:57,000
That's the trouble
with an infinite life

188
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:59,000
and a normal-sized memory.

189
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:02,720
It can't have been easy.
Outliving the people you love.

190
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:06,760
According to my journals, hell.

191
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:12,000
Sorry.

192
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:13,800
You'll have to remind me,

193
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,680
what's sorrow like?

194
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:19,160
It all just runs out, Doctor.

195
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:21,040
I'm just what's left.

196
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:25,040
In fact, I've done all I can here.

197
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:28,560
I look up to the sky and wonder
what it's like out there.

198
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:32,760
Please, take me with you.

199
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:35,600
All these people here,
they're like smoke,

200
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:37,080
they blow away in a moment.

201
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:40,040
-You don't know what it's like.
-I do know what it's like.

202
00:09:40,160 --> 00:09:42,120
Then, however you fly,

203
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:45,080
whatever ship you sail in,
take me with you.

204
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,440
How do you know I had a ship?

205
00:09:54,920 --> 00:09:57,720
Because I'm incredibly clever,
it doesn't matter.

206
00:09:58,680 --> 00:09:59,880
Take me with you.

207
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:01,240
We'll talk about it.

208
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:07,000
This thing you're looking for,
I'll help you find it, it'll be quicker.

209
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:09,240
-I don't need your help.
-Yes, you do.

210
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:10,960
I know where Lucie Fanshawe lives.

211
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:13,520
And I'm an excellent housebreaker.

212
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:15,040
We'll leave in an hour.

213
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:24,960
(DOOR CREAKING SHUT)

214
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:34,840
ME: Today is the day I should have died.

215
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:37,400
Instead, I was reborn.

216
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,200
By my hero, a man called the Doctor.

217
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:42,320
My love is dying.

218
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:44,960
It broke my heart
when the questions started

219
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:46,520
and I knew I had to leave him.

220
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:51,240
I return to find an old man
who smiles and thinks I am a dream.

221
00:10:51,880 --> 00:10:53,880
I am flesh and blood, my love,

222
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:56,640
but all you see is a ghost.

223
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:04,720
Tears.

224
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,040
ME: The plague.

225
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:15,320
-Mass graves.
-(WOMAN CRYING)

226
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,200
Sightless children...

227
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:19,240
DOCTOR: “...clutching toys
as they sleep,

228
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,520
"never to wake up.

229
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:23,800
"My children.

230
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:26,440
"My screams.

231
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,400
"I could not save you,

232
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:31,720
"little ones.

233
00:11:32,720 --> 00:11:34,000
"Such pain.

234
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:37,120
"And yet, still still

235
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:40,280
"I am not brave enough to die.

236
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:43,120
"To let go of this

237
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:45,080
"wretched life.

238
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:48,240
"I will endure,

239
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:52,000
"but no more babies.

240
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:55,920
-"I cannot, will not suffer...
-(SOBBING)

241
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,720
"...such heartbreak again.

242
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:06,920
"From now on,
it's me against the world."

243
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:09,240
(HEAVY BREATHING)

244
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:10,760
Quiet, my friend.

245
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:12,800
We have a visitor.

246
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:15,480
I didn't get it.

247
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:17,320
-But I will.
-(GROWLING)

248
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:19,920
If your promise stands,
I'll have it by dawn.

249
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,120
My visitor can help me.

250
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:23,920
Don't worry, he doesn't know about you.

251
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:26,680
Only about the artefact.

252
00:12:26,920 --> 00:12:29,520
He has no idea what we intend
to do with it.

253
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:36,680
(BLOWS)

254
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:40,680
I read your journals.

255
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:44,160
Why are there pages missing?

256
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:48,400
When things get really bad,
I tear the memories out.

257
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:53,160
What can be worse
than losing your children?

258
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:56,680
I keep that entry to remind me
not to have any more.

259
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:07,000
I've left you alone too long.

260
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:10,400
I had no idea how much you had suffered.

261
00:13:10,480 --> 00:13:12,520
But I remember the person
you used to be.

262
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:14,960
She's still in there.

263
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:18,320
-I can help you find her.
-Spare me your pity. I'm fine.

264
00:13:19,680 --> 00:13:22,240
I think this is just another mask
that you wear,

265
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:23,360
to protect you from the pain.

266
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:25,480
I think the alternative frightens you.

267
00:13:25,560 --> 00:13:27,160
That this is who I've become.

268
00:13:29,400 --> 00:13:31,280
This is no way to live your life.

269
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:33,320
Desensitised to the world.

270
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:34,640
So you intend to fix me?

271
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:37,840
Make me feel again?

272
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:39,840
Then run away?

273
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:43,960
I don't need your help, Doctor.
You need mine.

274
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:46,360
Just this once, you can't run off
like you usually do.

275
00:13:47,640 --> 00:13:50,880
How do you know?
How do you know what I usually do?

276
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:53,640
We met once in a Viking village.
I didn't give you my life story.

277
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:56,520
It's true, though, isn't it?

278
00:13:58,320 --> 00:13:59,560
You're the man who runs away.

279
00:14:00,120 --> 00:14:02,040
Oh, who told you that?

280
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:04,840
Maybe I just worked it out.

281
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:07,960
Come on.

282
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:17,720
(SNARLING)

283
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:28,440
(SNARLING)

284
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:32,600
ME: Housebreaks can be tricky.
DOCTOR: Not for me.

285
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:34,480
Sonic technology.

286
00:14:34,880 --> 00:14:37,280
Should be able to deactivate any alarms.

287
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:38,960
What's an alarm?

288
00:14:39,640 --> 00:14:40,960
The most wanted in the land.

289
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,720
Now is not the time to be showing off.

290
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:46,640
Now seems like a very good time to me.

291
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:49,000
You'll need a mask, sidekick.

292
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:52,480
-Watch and learn.
-Brought my own, thanks.

293
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:55,440
ME: 'Tis black as night.

294
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:57,520
I have a tinderbox somewhere.

295
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:03,120
(BUZZING)

296
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:06,400
Show-off.

297
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:08,520
Know where you're going, do you?

298
00:15:10,520 --> 00:15:12,320
The servants' stairs.

299
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:13,720
Follow me.

300
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:16,080
Why are you still alone?

301
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:17,920
What happened
to the second immortality charge

302
00:15:18,040 --> 00:15:19,440
-I gave you?
-Shh!

303
00:15:24,680 --> 00:15:25,920
No one's good enough.

304
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,160
-Humans need...
-Hush!

305
00:15:34,520 --> 00:15:36,400
(DOCTOR WHISPERING)
Humans need shared experiences...

306
00:15:36,480 --> 00:15:38,520
I'm regretting sharing this one.

307
00:15:39,880 --> 00:15:41,680
It isn't right for you
to be on your own.

308
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:44,040
-Goodnight, ma'am.
-(DOOR SHUTS)

309
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:55,280
I'll wager there's a dressing room.
Come on.

310
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:06,680
(DOOR CREAKING)

311
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:19,520
-(SCANNER BEEPING)
-(ME WHISPERING) Doctor!

312
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:21,560
Doctor, turn that thing off!

313
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:28,320
(BEEPING FASTER)

314
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:41,320
(PULSATING)

315
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:46,040
The Eyes of Hades.

316
00:16:54,960 --> 00:16:57,000
(DOOR UNLOCKING)

317
00:16:58,120 --> 00:17:00,120
-(BOTH GASPING)
-(BOTH PANTING)

318
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:08,600
(BOTH SIGHING)

319
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:10,760
(LOUD SNORING)

320
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:19,880
(WHISPERING) Let's just go around,
see if we can't get out the back.

321
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:22,000
Okay.

322
00:17:30,040 --> 00:17:31,040
(FLOORBOARD CREAKS)

323
00:17:31,120 --> 00:17:32,160
Lucie?

324
00:17:34,040 --> 00:17:35,440
(PANTING)

325
00:17:43,880 --> 00:17:45,080
Lucie?

326
00:17:51,120 --> 00:17:52,240
Lucie?

327
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,760
(DOOR OPENING AND SHUTTING)

328
00:18:03,760 --> 00:18:05,480
(SILVERWARE CLATTERING)

329
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:09,960
MR FANSHAWE: There is an intruder
on the premises!

330
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:11,720
Bring me my blunderbuss!

331
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:13,680
-What are you doing?
-It's kill or be killed.

332
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:16,560
(WHISPERING) No! You can't.
We should hide.

333
00:18:24,360 --> 00:18:25,600
Guard the doors!

334
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:27,240
Alert the militia!

335
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:30,880
Your feet, you oaf.
Oh, I said you'd be a liability.

336
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:33,000
Just let me shoot them
and be done with it.

337
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:36,240
(STRAINING) You're the liability.

338
00:18:36,320 --> 00:18:38,240
Never have this trouble with Clara.

339
00:18:38,320 --> 00:18:40,200
Oh, is she still with you is she?

340
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:41,280
(GRUNTS)

341
00:18:41,840 --> 00:18:43,080
Oh, you remember Clara, do you?

342
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:44,360
Of course.

343
00:18:44,640 --> 00:18:47,000
I take particular note
of anyone's weaknesses.

344
00:18:47,080 --> 00:18:49,440
MR FANSHAWE: Search every nook
and cranny!

345
00:18:49,640 --> 00:18:52,320
I warrant they will hang for this!

346
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:54,560
-So what's wrong with Clara, then?
-There's nothing wrong with her.

347
00:18:54,640 --> 00:18:55,880
Why haven't you made her immortal?

348
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:57,320
Well, look how you turned out.

349
00:18:57,400 --> 00:19:01,160
She'll die on you, you know.
She'll blow away like smoke.

350
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:02,520
Save your breath.

351
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:03,960
How old are you, Doctor?

352
00:19:04,040 --> 00:19:05,080
Older than you.

353
00:19:05,160 --> 00:19:06,680
How many have you lost?

354
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:07,960
How many Claras?

355
00:19:08,120 --> 00:19:10,320
(PANTING)

356
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:13,120
(BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY)

357
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:22,840
Robbery, burglary, that's capital.

358
00:19:23,240 --> 00:19:25,480
Meat and drink to the hangman, Ashildr.

359
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:26,840
I'm not Ashildr.

360
00:19:27,520 --> 00:19:31,360
I'm Me.
And I fear no hangman in Christendom.

361
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:34,720
Ah-ha!

362
00:19:35,920 --> 00:19:37,200
Sam Swift the Quick!

363
00:19:37,560 --> 00:19:39,120
I wouldn't be so bold, if I were you.

364
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:40,240
Don't you know who I am?

365
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:41,440
The Knightmare,

366
00:19:41,520 --> 00:19:42,720
which is why I'm not alone.

367
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:47,280
'Tis hardly a fair fight.

368
00:19:47,360 --> 00:19:49,320
And it was fair when you stole my patch?

369
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:50,920
Is that a fake nose, Sam?

370
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:52,960
Should call you Sam Sniffed.

371
00:19:53,040 --> 00:19:55,000
What's wrong with it,
it's perfectly normal, isn't it?

372
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:56,200
For an anteater, maybe.

373
00:19:56,280 --> 00:19:57,760
Ooh!

374
00:19:58,080 --> 00:20:01,240
Well, never knew
you were so puny, Knightmare.

375
00:20:01,320 --> 00:20:03,400
Or should I say, Slightmare.

376
00:20:03,480 --> 00:20:06,280
No, not the puns.
Line in the sand, no puns.

377
00:20:06,360 --> 00:20:08,480
It's what's in my brain
that counts, Bingo Boy.

378
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:10,680
Well, no brain
outwits a bullet, Dandiprat.

379
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:14,440
This is banter! I'm against banter!
I'm on record on the subject of banter.

380
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:17,080
Lay down your arms,
hand over the loot or I'll shoot.

381
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:18,920
(SIGHING) We'd better had.

382
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,880
He'll probably aim to miss
and hit one of us.

383
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:23,240
We could give you cash instead.

384
00:20:23,360 --> 00:20:25,040
Who's this? Your sidekick?

385
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:27,280
You got your dad as a sidekick?

386
00:20:27,360 --> 00:20:28,720
I'm not his dad, I'm the Doctor.

387
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:30,120
Is that the best name
you could come up with?

388
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:31,720
What, says "Sam Swift the Quick"?

389
00:20:32,560 --> 00:20:33,680
Trying a bit too hard, isn't it?

390
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:35,080
Or are you a little bit slow?

391
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:37,560
You what?

392
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:41,560
I rest my case.
No one outwits the Knightmare.

393
00:20:42,120 --> 00:20:43,280
Whoa!

394
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:49,600
If you value the life of your sidekick,
back off.

395
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:51,720
Put the weapon down...

396
00:20:52,720 --> 00:20:54,200
Who's slow now, Doctor?

397
00:20:54,280 --> 00:20:55,640
Whoa!

398
00:20:56,560 --> 00:20:58,080
-Good question.
-Please.

399
00:20:58,160 --> 00:21:00,440
Knightmare, I don't want to die.

400
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:02,280
Let's have honour amongst us.

401
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:03,640
Also, can you confirm
that I'm not your dad?

402
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:05,400
What do you say, Dad?

403
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:07,520
I should kill him?

404
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:10,080
He'll be dead in a minute,
what difference does it make?

405
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:12,360
Kill him and you make an enemy of me.

406
00:21:17,560 --> 00:21:18,720
Run.

407
00:21:28,480 --> 00:21:30,560
I know their lives are short.
I understand.

408
00:21:31,320 --> 00:21:32,680
But those lives do matter.

409
00:21:32,760 --> 00:21:33,880
Shut up.

410
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:35,760
You're not my dad.

411
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:51,280
I have a theory about the amulet.

412
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:53,040
(MAN COUGHING)

413
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:59,960
Morning, sir. Forgive me,
but might I enquire into who you are?

414
00:22:00,640 --> 00:22:01,760
The Doctor.

415
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:03,520
Clayton, sir.

416
00:22:06,960 --> 00:22:09,600
-Would you care for a cocktail, my lady?
-Oh, yes, please.

417
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:14,200
(CLAYTON COUGHING)

418
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:16,800
Half-blind and deaf as a post.

419
00:22:17,320 --> 00:22:18,920
He's no use any more really but...

420
00:22:19,160 --> 00:22:20,280
You keep him on.

421
00:22:20,760 --> 00:22:22,440
See? You do have a heart.
You don't fool me.

422
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:24,880
-How do I look?
-Pink.

423
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:26,520
Are you coming down with something?

424
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:30,240
Look, why would an alien artefact
resemble the Eyes of Hades,

425
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:31,600
King of the Underworld?

426
00:22:32,760 --> 00:22:35,640
An ancient Greek talisman
which wards off evil

427
00:22:35,720 --> 00:22:39,000
and protects those in death
on their journey to an afterlife.

428
00:22:39,080 --> 00:22:40,280
You tell me.

429
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:43,920
Could it be that the mythology
originated on another planet?

430
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:47,400
You can't wait to get going
and find out, I'll wager.

431
00:22:47,480 --> 00:22:50,840
No. I think I want to stick around,

432
00:22:50,920 --> 00:22:52,400
keep an eye on you for a while.

433
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:53,880
Get me back on track.

434
00:22:53,960 --> 00:22:55,040
Well, why not?

435
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:56,880
Hey, we're a good team.

436
00:22:58,040 --> 00:22:59,400
Then take me with you.

437
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:03,040
You don't want to be stuck
with an old fool like me,

438
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:06,040
you have this whole wonderful planet
to play on...

439
00:23:06,120 --> 00:23:08,040
It takes a day to get to Kent.

440
00:23:08,320 --> 00:23:09,360
In the future, you'll fly.

441
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:11,000
I want to fly right now.

442
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:18,720
(RAGGED BREATHING) I have waited longer
than I should have ever lived.

443
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:24,040
I have lost more
than I can even remember.

444
00:23:25,080 --> 00:23:27,480
(SOBBING)
Please, Doctor,

445
00:23:29,640 --> 00:23:31,120
just get me out of this.

446
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:35,360
I want more than this.
I deserve more than this.

447
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:38,800
Why not?

448
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:43,680
Why not?

449
00:23:44,960 --> 00:23:46,880
Because it wouldn't be good.

450
00:23:55,040 --> 00:23:56,320
Ashildr, please.

451
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:00,040
Ashildr...

452
00:24:00,120 --> 00:24:04,400
I am not Ashildr any more.

453
00:24:04,720 --> 00:24:06,480
(FAINT GROWLING)

454
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:09,040
Do you have a cat?

455
00:24:11,360 --> 00:24:12,720
Sounds like a very big cat.

456
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:15,480
-(LOUD GROWLING)
-Hence, the very big cat flap.

457
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:31,920
Leandro, meet the Doctor.

458
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:35,000
You thought I was helping you.

459
00:24:35,440 --> 00:24:37,200
In fact, it was the other way around.

460
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:38,680
Leandro, we have it.

461
00:24:38,760 --> 00:24:40,560
My friend here
was as useful as I'd hoped.

462
00:24:40,760 --> 00:24:43,480
If somebody needed my help,
why did nobody just ask?

463
00:24:43,880 --> 00:24:47,240
I am forced to assume that you have
plans that I wouldn't approve.

464
00:24:47,320 --> 00:24:49,200
-Oh, Ashildr.
-Stop calling me that.

465
00:24:53,320 --> 00:24:54,760
-Kill me.
-Why?

466
00:24:54,840 --> 00:24:56,920
If you intend any harm to this planet
or its people,

467
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:58,680
then killing me is by far
your best move.

468
00:24:58,760 --> 00:24:59,960
You invite your own death?

469
00:25:00,040 --> 00:25:02,680
No, I just want you to attack first.
Then my conscience is clear.

470
00:25:02,760 --> 00:25:03,880
-Of what?
-You.

471
00:25:03,960 --> 00:25:06,000
(LEANDRO LAUGHING)

472
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:09,160
You are not of this world
or part of my plans.

473
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:11,120
I have no quarrel with you.

474
00:25:11,200 --> 00:25:13,040
Then tell me why you are here
and what you intend to do.

475
00:25:13,120 --> 00:25:15,440
Otherwise, get on
with trying to kill me,

476
00:25:15,520 --> 00:25:18,200
but I advise you,
be very quick and very sure.

477
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:20,240
I am from Delta Leonis.

478
00:25:20,320 --> 00:25:21,920
My tribe was overthrown,

479
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:25,920
my world destroyed,
my wife killed as we escaped.

480
00:25:26,160 --> 00:25:28,200
Using the amulet?
That was your means of travel.

481
00:25:28,280 --> 00:25:30,720
I lost it when I crashed to earth.

482
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:32,320
I found him in my grounds.

483
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:34,440
He's been sleeping there
while I searched for it.

484
00:25:34,520 --> 00:25:36,040
The underworld.

485
00:25:36,120 --> 00:25:37,480
Gateway to an afterlife.

486
00:25:38,080 --> 00:25:40,480
-Another reality.
-We need it to open a portal.

487
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:42,880
-Travel the galaxy.
-Oh!

488
00:25:42,960 --> 00:25:44,800
Oh, so what's the plan, Ashildr?

489
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:46,640
Fancy yourself as his new queen?

490
00:25:46,760 --> 00:25:48,640
Hunting, running errands
while he sleeps.

491
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:49,760
Oh, dear God.

492
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:52,400
You're just like every other man.

493
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:54,840
I'm not looking for a husband, you oaf.

494
00:25:54,920 --> 00:25:56,880
I'm looking
for a horse to get me out of town.

495
00:25:57,640 --> 00:26:00,000
-You said no.
-What? Do you think you can trust him?

496
00:26:00,080 --> 00:26:01,800
He knows what it is to be alone.

497
00:26:01,880 --> 00:26:02,920
So do 1.

498
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,680
Then how could you do what you did?

499
00:26:04,960 --> 00:26:06,560
-I'm looking for the headline here.
-ME: The what?

500
00:26:06,640 --> 00:26:07,920
Well, you know, you want to escape?

501
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:09,200
Well, go on, escape as much as you like!

502
00:26:09,280 --> 00:26:10,800
Why would I not approve?

503
00:26:11,720 --> 00:26:13,120
-The amulet...
-What about it?

504
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:14,480
A death is required.

505
00:26:14,560 --> 00:26:16,520
It is the only way the amulet works.

506
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:17,640
Of course.

507
00:26:18,120 --> 00:26:21,240
Every single death is a tiny fracture
in reality.

508
00:26:21,320 --> 00:26:23,800
And the amulet
can lever the fracture open.

509
00:26:23,880 --> 00:26:25,360
Primitive, but effective.

510
00:26:25,440 --> 00:26:27,760
It's just exploiting
an abundant resource.

511
00:26:28,360 --> 00:26:30,320
-There's so much dying here.
-So who dies,

512
00:26:30,640 --> 00:26:32,280
SO you can run away?

513
00:26:33,360 --> 00:26:34,760
Clayton?

514
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:37,200
CLAYTON: (COUGHING) Coming, my lady.

515
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:39,640
No, you can't, he loves you.

516
00:26:39,760 --> 00:26:41,120
To the end, it would seem.

517
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:42,680
Would you rather take his place?

518
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:44,280
(ROARING)

519
00:26:44,360 --> 00:26:46,080
Not the Doctor, we agreed.

520
00:26:47,160 --> 00:26:48,360
(GROWLING)

521
00:26:48,720 --> 00:26:50,480
Ashildr, daughter of Einarr,

522
00:26:50,760 --> 00:26:52,120
what happened to you?

523
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:54,920
You did, Doctor.

524
00:26:56,120 --> 00:26:57,120
You happened.

525
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:03,560
I know you've suffered.

526
00:27:04,040 --> 00:27:05,120
Your children dying.

527
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:08,800
They would have died anyway.

528
00:27:09,840 --> 00:27:11,200
Human life is fleeting.

529
00:27:11,760 --> 00:27:16,240
People are mayflies, breeding and dying,
repeating the same mistakes.

530
00:27:16,720 --> 00:27:17,800
It's boring.

531
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:19,800
And I am stuck here.

532
00:27:20,120 --> 00:27:21,120
Abandoned.

533
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:24,440
By the one man who should know
what eternity feels like.

534
00:27:25,120 --> 00:27:26,160
Who should understand.

535
00:27:26,760 --> 00:27:28,760
I do, now. But...

536
00:27:28,840 --> 00:27:30,400
You still won't take me with you.

537
00:27:32,480 --> 00:27:34,200
You gad about,

538
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:39,040
while I trudge through the centuries,
day by day.

539
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:41,280
Hour by hour.

540
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:46,000
Do you ever think or care
what happens after you've flown away?

541
00:27:47,440 --> 00:27:49,440
I live in the world you leave behind.

542
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:52,920
Because you abandoned me to it.

543
00:27:53,240 --> 00:27:54,760
Why should I be responsible for you?

544
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:57,440
-You made me immortal!
-I saved your life.

545
00:27:58,240 --> 00:28:01,840
I didn't know your heart would rust
because I kept it beating.

546
00:28:02,680 --> 00:28:05,840
I didn't think that your conscience
would need renewing,

547
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:08,480
or that the well of human kindness
would run dry.

548
00:28:10,560 --> 00:28:14,280
I just wanted
to save a terrified young woman's life.

549
00:28:15,480 --> 00:28:17,280
You didn't save my life, Doctor.

550
00:28:19,960 --> 00:28:21,600
You trapped me inside it.

551
00:28:24,480 --> 00:28:26,440
And now I found someone
who will set me free.

552
00:28:26,520 --> 00:28:27,800
Someone who understands.

553
00:28:27,880 --> 00:28:29,120
Look, I don't know what Lenny the Lion
is up to,

554
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:30,440
but I know his type.

555
00:28:30,560 --> 00:28:33,160
Very first argument,
guaranteed he'll bite your head off.

556
00:28:33,240 --> 00:28:34,400
Or I'll bite his off.

557
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:36,800
Perhaps I'll enjoy that.

558
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:38,360
You're playing with fire.

559
00:28:38,440 --> 00:28:42,760
Open that portal, you have no idea
what horrors might come through.

560
00:28:42,840 --> 00:28:45,120
That's as good a reason as any to do it.

561
00:28:45,280 --> 00:28:46,480
You're not like this. I know you're not.

562
00:28:46,560 --> 00:28:48,680
This is exactly what I'm like.

563
00:28:49,240 --> 00:28:51,560
This is what you made of me.

564
00:28:53,320 --> 00:28:54,640
He'll kill you.

565
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:57,160
He'll have to be fast.

566
00:28:57,760 --> 00:28:58,800
And if he does...

567
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:01,120
Perhaps it's about time.

568
00:29:02,120 --> 00:29:03,480
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

569
00:29:03,560 --> 00:29:05,320
MAN: Lady Me?

570
00:29:10,200 --> 00:29:12,520
Oh, Lady Me,
thank goodness you are safe.

571
00:29:12,880 --> 00:29:14,600
Sam Swift has been captured,

572
00:29:14,680 --> 00:29:17,360
and he swore the Knightmare
was heading in this direction.

573
00:29:17,440 --> 00:29:18,560
I've not seen him.

574
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:20,880
Sam Swift will hang in Tyburn at noon.

575
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:23,000
In half an hour?

576
00:29:24,520 --> 00:29:26,400
A guilty man, destined to die,

577
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:27,560
no harm in that.

578
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:28,720
I've not seen the Knightmare.

579
00:29:29,240 --> 00:29:31,000
But this is his sidekick, the Doctor.

580
00:29:31,160 --> 00:29:32,440
He was robbing me.

581
00:29:32,640 --> 00:29:34,280
I only just managed to overpower him.

582
00:29:36,520 --> 00:29:37,800
-You will hang for this.
-No.

583
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:39,440
Listen, I was trying to help her.

584
00:29:39,520 --> 00:29:40,720
Silence or we'll...

585
00:29:43,640 --> 00:29:44,680
Shoot.

586
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:50,240
He needn't hang. But keep him
under lock and key for all our sakes.

587
00:29:50,640 --> 00:29:51,960
(DOOR CREAKING OPEN)

588
00:29:53,120 --> 00:29:54,240
Was that the door?

589
00:29:55,520 --> 00:29:58,200
Oh, dear. Always the quiet ones.

590
00:29:58,640 --> 00:29:59,680
Goodbye, Clayton.

591
00:30:00,840 --> 00:30:02,520
You see? I do have a heart.

592
00:30:02,800 --> 00:30:04,160
In which case, don't do it.

593
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:19,920
Do I look like some feckless thief?

594
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:21,000
I'm on your side,

595
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:24,040
I'm an undercover constable
from Scotland Yard.

596
00:30:25,640 --> 00:30:26,760
Do you have Scotland Yard yet?

597
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:28,720
Been on the cider, have we? (LAUGHS)

598
00:30:29,760 --> 00:30:31,160
The Dunbar victory medal.

599
00:30:32,560 --> 00:30:34,240
I was decorated for valour in battle.

600
00:30:34,520 --> 00:30:35,720
Tell it to the Newgate jailer.

601
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:37,800
All I want is to bring
the Knightmare to justice.

602
00:30:37,880 --> 00:30:39,240
But you were robbing Lady Me.

603
00:30:39,320 --> 00:30:41,200
I came to warn her.
I fear her life is in danger.

604
00:30:42,040 --> 00:30:44,560
Look, it's the Knightmare.

605
00:30:44,640 --> 00:30:47,720
Cloaked and in disguise, bound
for Tyburn. You have to let me go.

606
00:30:47,800 --> 00:30:48,880
Or take me there.

607
00:30:48,960 --> 00:30:50,160
You wish to hang, too?

608
00:30:51,360 --> 00:30:52,880
Will you take me there if I say yes?

609
00:30:52,960 --> 00:30:56,080
Indeed. There's a bounty
on your head for £20.

610
00:30:56,960 --> 00:30:58,600
Twenty pounds? Is that all?

611
00:30:58,680 --> 00:31:00,560
'Tis a small fortune to us.

612
00:31:00,640 --> 00:31:04,440
Well, in that case, I know where
Lady Me keeps all of her money.

613
00:31:05,440 --> 00:31:06,920
Almost £30.

614
00:31:07,720 --> 00:31:10,480
Now, why didn't you
say that in the first place?

615
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:13,760
(BREATHING STRENUOUSLY)

616
00:31:21,800 --> 00:31:23,320
(CROWD BOOING AND JEERING)

617
00:31:23,640 --> 00:31:25,680
(INDISTINCT YELLING)

618
00:31:27,240 --> 00:31:28,480
Hang him!

619
00:31:30,960 --> 00:31:33,280
MAN: All right, calm down, steady on.

620
00:31:36,920 --> 00:31:39,120
Such a good turnout. I'm honoured.

621
00:31:39,560 --> 00:31:42,080
(LAUGHS) Oh, yeah.

622
00:31:42,440 --> 00:31:45,640
Hey, he's new at this,
someone had to show him the ropes.

623
00:31:45,720 --> 00:31:47,040
(CROWD LAUGHS)

624
00:31:47,120 --> 00:31:48,880
Don't worry, mate,
you'll get the hang of it.

625
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:59,040
When I'm gone, they'll all say
that Sam Swift, he was well hung.

626
00:31:59,120 --> 00:32:00,960
(CROWD LAUGHING)

627
00:32:01,040 --> 00:32:03,080
Well, I think a few of you
know that already.

628
00:32:03,160 --> 00:32:06,560
(LAUGHS) Oh, yeah, I'm sure
I recognise a few of you lovely ladies.

629
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:08,960
You, and you.

630
00:32:09,040 --> 00:32:11,840
I mean, I'd introduce you all,
but I can't remember your names.

631
00:32:11,920 --> 00:32:14,240
(CROWD BOOING)

632
00:32:15,960 --> 00:32:16,960
(GRUNTS)

633
00:32:17,040 --> 00:32:18,600
It's a good job you're here,
or they'd kill me.

634
00:32:19,720 --> 00:32:21,160
(BELL TOLLS)

635
00:32:25,840 --> 00:32:26,880
-(NEIGHING)
-(GRUNTS)

636
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:32,360
-(BELL TOLLING)
-(MAN YELLING)

637
00:32:34,480 --> 00:32:38,400
Mary, Meg, help me out here, miss.

638
00:32:38,480 --> 00:32:40,240
That's Mrs Baxter to you.

639
00:32:40,320 --> 00:32:41,400
That's a funny name for a fellow.

640
00:32:41,480 --> 00:32:42,680
(CROWD LAUGHS)

641
00:32:42,840 --> 00:32:43,840
It's time.

642
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:46,560
SWIFT: I've got plenty more,
jokes that is, as well as women.

643
00:32:46,640 --> 00:32:48,200
Hang him now!

644
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:50,840
CROWD: Hang him! Hang him!

645
00:32:55,240 --> 00:32:56,240
(URGING HORSE ALONG)

646
00:32:57,800 --> 00:32:59,360
MAN: Make us laugh, Sam.

647
00:33:00,560 --> 00:33:03,440
Aye, for while you laugh, I live.

648
00:33:05,480 --> 00:33:07,520
It was raining on the way over here.

649
00:33:07,600 --> 00:33:09,040
The hangman says to me,

650
00:33:09,120 --> 00:33:11,120
"It's all right for you,
I've got to walk back through this."

651
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:12,840
(CROWD LAUGHS)

652
00:33:17,200 --> 00:33:18,760
What are you paying for, my beauty?

653
00:33:18,840 --> 00:33:22,680
To make it quick.
A fitting end for you, Sam Swift.

654
00:33:23,960 --> 00:33:25,960
Who should be the last
to kiss these lips?

655
00:33:26,080 --> 00:33:27,520
WOMEN IN CROWD: Me! Me!

656
00:33:27,600 --> 00:33:28,840
They must mean you, Lady Me.

657
00:33:35,640 --> 00:33:37,000
You remind me of someone.

658
00:33:38,280 --> 00:33:39,960
Now I want to live more than ever.

659
00:33:40,040 --> 00:33:42,000
DOCTOR: Sorry, yes, yes,
sorry about the horse, excuse me.

660
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:44,360
Sorry, excuse me, excuse me! Sorry.

661
00:33:44,440 --> 00:33:46,080
Time to hang!

662
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:52,320
All right, all right.

663
00:33:52,840 --> 00:33:56,280
As God is my highwayman,
he steals the most precious gift of all.

664
00:33:57,760 --> 00:33:58,760
Life.

665
00:33:59,240 --> 00:34:01,960
Magical, filled with adventures.

666
00:34:02,640 --> 00:34:04,520
But at least I can say
that I lived mine to the full.

667
00:34:05,120 --> 00:34:06,560
WOMAN: I love you, Sam Swift!

668
00:34:10,800 --> 00:34:15,200
Is that the Doctor? Doctor, Doctor!
I'm a robber!

669
00:34:20,640 --> 00:34:22,120
Have you taken anything for it?

670
00:34:22,680 --> 00:34:24,160
(CROWD LAUGHS)

671
00:34:24,440 --> 00:34:26,040
Doctor, Doctor!

672
00:34:26,120 --> 00:34:28,720
-Quick, I'm running out of patients.
-(CROWD LAUGHS)

673
00:34:29,040 --> 00:34:31,200
Have you ever seen a sidekick so old?

674
00:34:31,600 --> 00:34:32,840
I'm no one's sidekick!

675
00:34:32,920 --> 00:34:35,680
-He's so old, he farts dust!
-(CROWD LAUGHS)

676
00:34:36,320 --> 00:34:38,840
His nose is so big that...

677
00:34:38,920 --> 00:34:40,600
They'll have to widen the noose.

678
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:43,400
Or bury him in a pyramid.

679
00:34:43,600 --> 00:34:45,440
You know what they say? Big nose...

680
00:34:46,080 --> 00:34:48,400
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

681
00:34:48,840 --> 00:34:50,680
-Big handkerchief?
-(CROWD LAUGHS)

682
00:34:51,480 --> 00:34:53,720
No, Doctor, don't leave me hanging.

683
00:34:54,760 --> 00:34:57,880
I have a pardon here for Sam Swift,
from Cromwell himself.

684
00:35:03,640 --> 00:35:05,120
Sam Swift is pardoned.

685
00:35:05,200 --> 00:35:07,440
(CROWD BOOS)

686
00:35:07,520 --> 00:35:10,480
MAN: We didn't come
all this way not to see someone hang!

687
00:35:10,560 --> 00:35:11,800
What about the Doctor?

688
00:35:12,560 --> 00:35:14,960
CROWD: Hang the Doctor! Hang the Doctor!

689
00:35:15,040 --> 00:35:17,040
(CROWD YELLING)

690
00:35:17,120 --> 00:35:18,280
Shh.

691
00:35:20,560 --> 00:35:22,000
You want to see someone die?

692
00:35:24,400 --> 00:35:25,680
How's this?

693
00:35:25,760 --> 00:35:27,640
No, Ashildr, no!

694
00:35:27,720 --> 00:35:28,880
No!

695
00:35:40,680 --> 00:35:42,480
DOCTOR: Purple, colour of death.

696
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:47,120
His life force is opening a portal.

697
00:35:47,720 --> 00:35:49,040
ME: To my new life.

698
00:35:49,160 --> 00:35:50,160
Or to hell.

699
00:35:50,880 --> 00:35:52,120
(ROARING)

700
00:35:53,360 --> 00:35:54,360
A lion man!

701
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:56,000
(THUNDER CRASHING)

702
00:35:57,560 --> 00:35:58,720
Look!

703
00:36:02,720 --> 00:36:03,760
Goodbye, Doctor.

704
00:36:03,840 --> 00:36:05,640
You are going nowhere.

705
00:36:05,720 --> 00:36:06,920
Doors work both ways.

706
00:36:08,080 --> 00:36:10,320
They let people out,
and they let the enemy in.

707
00:36:10,400 --> 00:36:12,840
ME: What's that? What's happening?
What are those things?

708
00:36:12,920 --> 00:36:15,600
Spaceships, or they will be.
They're coming through the rift

709
00:36:15,680 --> 00:36:17,760
actualising in this plane of reality.

710
00:36:17,840 --> 00:36:19,560
You said you were
the last of the Leonians.

711
00:36:20,240 --> 00:36:23,720
-We were meant to escape!
-You shall, in death.

712
00:36:24,640 --> 00:36:26,800
(CROWD SCREAMING)

713
00:36:35,520 --> 00:36:36,560
No!

714
00:36:39,760 --> 00:36:42,760
Doctor, what have I done?
What have I done to these people?

715
00:36:45,120 --> 00:36:47,200
Stop this! They are defenceless.

716
00:36:48,920 --> 00:36:49,920
Ashildr!

717
00:36:52,280 --> 00:36:54,160
-He doesn't care.
-But I do.

718
00:36:55,120 --> 00:36:58,960
Oh, God, I do. I actually do, I care.

719
00:36:59,520 --> 00:37:01,680
It's awful, isn't it? It's infuriating.

720
00:37:02,080 --> 00:37:04,880
You think you don't care,
but then you fall off the wagon.

721
00:37:04,960 --> 00:37:06,920
Never mind about me,
what are we gonna do about them?

722
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:08,760
We have to help them, they need you.

723
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:10,880
They need us!

724
00:37:11,560 --> 00:37:14,280
-Welcome back.
-Well, do something then!

725
00:37:14,400 --> 00:37:18,440
Okay, okay, um, Eyes of Hades,

726
00:37:18,680 --> 00:37:22,080
afterlife, death opens up a gateway...
We need to close it.

727
00:37:22,200 --> 00:37:25,040
-Yeah, I know, but how?
-Sam Swift, he's the conduit.

728
00:37:25,120 --> 00:37:26,520
The amulet, it's still in him.

729
00:37:26,600 --> 00:37:30,040
It's his death that's opening the rift.
So, what do we do?

730
00:37:30,680 --> 00:37:33,120
-Reverse it.
-You cannot reverse death.

731
00:37:33,360 --> 00:37:34,760
Oh, yes, we can.

732
00:37:37,600 --> 00:37:38,600
DOCTOR: Run!

733
00:37:44,760 --> 00:37:48,120
No, my lady,
they will destroy me for this.

734
00:37:52,040 --> 00:37:53,920
The light of immortality.

735
00:37:59,520 --> 00:38:00,840
(ROARING)

736
00:38:02,400 --> 00:38:03,880
Spare me, my brothers!

737
00:38:24,280 --> 00:38:25,280
SAM: Alive.

738
00:38:29,080 --> 00:38:30,200
I'm alive!

739
00:38:30,360 --> 00:38:33,240
-(LAUGHS)
-(CROWD CHEERS)

740
00:38:51,920 --> 00:38:54,120
Last thing I remember
is you turning up, Doctor.

741
00:38:55,320 --> 00:38:58,120
Good thing, too. Between you and me,
I was running out of material.

742
00:38:58,200 --> 00:39:01,000
I could tell, gave a whole
new meaning to dying on stage.

743
00:39:01,080 --> 00:39:02,920
Gallows humour can be tricky.

744
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:04,880
But at least
there's never a second house.

745
00:39:05,800 --> 00:39:07,880
We've nearly finished these,
I'll get some more in.

746
00:39:09,040 --> 00:39:11,960
By the way,
I've not forgotten that kiss.

747
00:39:17,560 --> 00:39:19,920
-Is he immortal now?
-Do you want him to be?

748
00:39:20,520 --> 00:39:22,000
I don't think I want anyone to be.

749
00:39:23,440 --> 00:39:24,440
Well, probably not.

750
00:39:24,600 --> 00:39:25,880
Probably the power
would have been drained

751
00:39:25,960 --> 00:39:29,160
by the whole opening
and reversing the portal thingy.

752
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:31,720
There'll be enough power
to bring him back,

753
00:39:31,800 --> 00:39:35,760
but not enough power
to keep him here. Probably.

754
00:39:37,160 --> 00:39:39,040
-Did you just make all of that up?
-Yeah.

755
00:39:39,840 --> 00:39:42,880
It's hard to keep track
of all this stuff.

756
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:46,360
Keep an eye on him though,
he might be around for a while. Or not.

757
00:39:46,560 --> 00:39:47,560
Who can say?

758
00:39:53,120 --> 00:39:55,760
You're still not going
to take me with you, are you?

759
00:40:01,760 --> 00:40:04,240
People like us, we go on too long.

760
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:07,520
We forget what matters.

761
00:40:12,160 --> 00:40:14,200
The last thing we need is each other.

762
00:40:15,440 --> 00:40:16,680
We need the mayflies.

763
00:40:20,040 --> 00:40:22,600
See, the mayflies,
they know more than we do.

764
00:40:24,160 --> 00:40:27,200
They know how beautiful and precious
life is because it's fleeting.

765
00:40:30,880 --> 00:40:34,760
Look how Sam Swift made every
last moment count, right to the gallows.

766
00:40:36,160 --> 00:40:38,280
Look how glad he is to be alive.

767
00:40:42,640 --> 00:40:46,120
I looked into your eyes
and I saw my worst fears.

768
00:40:47,240 --> 00:40:51,200
Weariness, emptiness.

769
00:40:52,720 --> 00:40:55,160
That's why you can't travel with me.

770
00:40:55,840 --> 00:40:58,760
Our perspectives are too vast,
too far away.

771
00:41:03,520 --> 00:41:06,920
You're not first, you know.
I did travel with another immortal once.

772
00:41:07,920 --> 00:41:09,400
Captain Jack Harkness.

773
00:41:10,240 --> 00:41:11,240
Who?

774
00:41:12,960 --> 00:41:13,960
(SCOFFS)

775
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:16,320
He'll get 'round to you, eventually.

776
00:41:18,240 --> 00:41:20,080
Who told you about me?

777
00:41:20,520 --> 00:41:23,520
The man who comes for the battle
and runs away from the fallout.

778
00:41:26,360 --> 00:41:27,360
Take your pick.

779
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:32,360
You've had an impact on this world.
You've made waves.

780
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:35,000
Sometimes tidal waves.

781
00:41:36,160 --> 00:41:38,520
-I'm flattered.
-Well, you should be.

782
00:41:38,600 --> 00:41:40,360
You're an extraordinary woman, Ashildr,

783
00:41:42,040 --> 00:41:46,280
but I think I'm gonna
have to keep an eye on you.

784
00:41:48,080 --> 00:41:50,600
-No.
-No?

785
00:41:50,680 --> 00:41:53,000
Someone has to look out
for the people you abandon.

786
00:41:54,200 --> 00:41:57,920
Who better than me? I'll be the patron
saint of the Doctor's leftovers.

787
00:41:58,760 --> 00:42:00,720
While you're busy protecting this world,

788
00:42:01,680 --> 00:42:03,800
I'll get busy protecting it from you.

789
00:42:06,280 --> 00:42:07,760
So, are we enemies now?

790
00:42:09,200 --> 00:42:10,560
Of course not.

791
00:42:12,080 --> 00:42:14,120
Enemies are never a problem.

792
00:42:15,680 --> 00:42:17,480
It's your friends
you have to watch out for.

793
00:42:17,960 --> 00:42:19,680
And, my friend,

794
00:42:20,960 --> 00:42:22,600
I'll be watching out for you.

795
00:42:24,920 --> 00:42:25,920
Ashildr,

796
00:42:28,440 --> 00:42:30,480
I think I'm very glad I saved you.

797
00:42:31,840 --> 00:42:33,280
Oh, I think everyone will be.

798
00:42:35,840 --> 00:42:37,280
(GUITAR STRUMS)

799
00:42:49,880 --> 00:42:51,240
(DOOR OPENS)

800
00:42:51,320 --> 00:42:53,040
Hey! Hello?

801
00:42:53,320 --> 00:42:55,360
Oh, hello! Hi!

802
00:42:55,880 --> 00:42:58,720
-Did you miss me?
-Be more specific. Who are you?

803
00:42:58,800 --> 00:43:00,600
Ha-ha. I've got a present for you.

804
00:43:00,680 --> 00:43:02,480
-Why, am I ill? Are you ill?
-No. No.

805
00:43:02,560 --> 00:43:04,720
Are you never gonna travel
with me again because I said a thing?

806
00:43:04,800 --> 00:43:06,200
It's not a good present.

807
00:43:06,280 --> 00:43:07,280
Oh, well, that's a relief.

808
00:43:07,360 --> 00:43:08,720
Okay, Evie Hubbard.

809
00:43:08,800 --> 00:43:10,400
Year seven.
You helped her out with her homework?

810
00:43:10,480 --> 00:43:12,200
Imaginary interview
with Winston Churchill?

811
00:43:12,280 --> 00:43:13,920
-You basically cheated.
-That was her fault.

812
00:43:14,000 --> 00:43:15,640
Because she should
have stressed "imaginary".

813
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:18,360
Anyway, she got an A and so,

814
00:43:18,680 --> 00:43:21,520
(CHUCKLES)
she has sent you a selfie.

815
00:43:22,680 --> 00:43:24,360
Yes, you're right,
that is not a good present.

816
00:43:24,480 --> 00:43:26,600
-Come on.
-Do they make sherbet lemons any more?

817
00:43:26,680 --> 00:43:28,480
And I'd like a Ferrari,
what about a Ferrari?

818
00:43:28,560 --> 00:43:29,640
I knew you'd be thrilled.

819
00:43:29,760 --> 00:43:32,320
Okay, come on, let me see,
let me see, let me see.

820
00:43:32,880 --> 00:43:33,880
(LAUGHS)

821
00:43:34,680 --> 00:43:35,680
(CHUCKLES)

822
00:43:43,600 --> 00:43:44,600
What's wrong?

823
00:43:46,200 --> 00:43:48,640
Nothing. Nothing at all.

824
00:43:49,760 --> 00:43:52,640
-Doctor?
-Tell her, next time, I'll take cash.

825
00:43:54,240 --> 00:43:55,240
So...

826
00:43:56,920 --> 00:43:58,880
-Where are you gonna take me?
-Wherever you want.

827
00:43:59,440 --> 00:44:00,840
Hmm. Somewhere...

828
00:44:02,080 --> 00:44:03,080
Somewhere magical.

829
00:44:04,240 --> 00:44:05,280
Somewhere new.

830
00:44:05,360 --> 00:44:07,600
Ah, there is nowhere new under the sun.

831
00:44:08,480 --> 00:44:09,840
Above it, on the other hand,

832
00:44:16,360 --> 00:44:18,440
I've missed you, Clara Oswald.

833
00:44:20,520 --> 00:44:24,640
Well, don't worry, daft old man,
I'm not going anywhere.

834
00:44:37,000 --> 00:44:39,440
OSGOOD: Twenty million Zygons have been
allowed to take human form,

835
00:44:39,520 --> 00:44:40,600
and are now living amongst us.

836
00:44:40,720 --> 00:44:43,640
WOMAN: Any living thing in this world,
including my family and friends,

837
00:44:43,720 --> 00:44:45,600
could turn into a Zygon and kill me.

838
00:44:45,720 --> 00:44:47,320
It's not paranoia when it's real.

839
00:44:47,560 --> 00:44:48,720
They've kidnapped Osgood

840
00:44:48,800 --> 00:44:51,240
and they've stolen the location
of every Zygon on earth.

841
00:44:51,320 --> 00:44:53,560
-Doctor, the ceasefire's broken down.
-Run away!

842
00:44:53,720 --> 00:44:55,320
We have a Zygon revolution on our hands.

843
00:44:55,600 --> 00:44:58,000
ZYGON: We've won the first battle.

844
00:44:58,080 --> 00:44:59,200
There will be truce.

845
00:44:59,280 --> 00:45:02,200
ZYGON: And now
we are going to begin the war.

846
00:45:02,320 --> 00:45:03,920
WOMAN: Or there will be consequences.

847
00:45:04,000 --> 00:45:05,560
-CLARA: I think you might be right?
-About what?

848
00:45:06,080 --> 00:45:07,280
The end of the world.

